Smiley senior Yucon is a super sweet and affectionate gentleman. At 10 years of age, he has playful tendencies and bursts of energy that prove age is just a number! This happy meatball is 74 pounds but thinks he is a lap dog and likes to climb onto your lap for smooches if you give him the chance. üòô He is calm and easygoing, already knows how to sit and walks well on leash. Talk about a silver fox! Yucon has been waiting at the shelter since December 2, 2017 and is so ready to find a home of his own. All of our dogs deserve a home with a soft warm bed to call their own, but this is especially true for seniors! Come in to meet dear Mr. Yucon today!
Yucon is *Blue/Medically Alerted for geriatric, worn teeth*. SHARE to help his special family find him!

These pictures were taken a year ago, the day that Charlie stole my heart and came into our family. That day, I went to the store to buy a safety harness for Daisy, and while there I met Charlie (then named Penny) at an adoption drive... she stole my heart immediately. So, that day I returned home with a new puppy. Sometimes life comes with the most amazing surprises.
